{
  "id": "3",
  "title": "3. Secure Database Connectors",
  "type": "lab",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "## Designing Safe Database Connectors"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Giving AI agents access to databases creates powerful opportunities, but exposing tables without security controls risks data loss or exfiltration. Because AI models are vulnerable to prompt injection, a user could manipulate the model to execute destructive DDL commands (e.g., 'DROP TABLE') or read sensitive data. As a Systems Integrator, you must design a secure layer to mitigate these risks."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> [!WARNING]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> Never connect an MCP server to a database using administrator credentials. Implement read-only database user accounts and use parameterized inputs to prevent SQL injection."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "### Access Layer Design Principles"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- Least Privilege User: Use credentials that restrict the server's database access to a whitelist of tables."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- Parameterized Query Construction: Never construct queries by concatenating raw strings. Always use bind parameters."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- Dynamic Schema Exposure: Query database metadata tables to dynamically list schemas as Resources, guiding the model's queries."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- Execution Limits: Enforce limits on row counts (e.g., LIMIT 50) and statement timeouts (e.g., 500ms) to prevent performance issues."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "### Implementing the Database Server"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "The following TypeScript server connects to PostgreSQL with read-only credentials, exposing schemas as Read-only Resources and using parameterized queries to fetch data safely:"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "```typescript"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "import { Server } from \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/index.js\";"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "import { StdioServerTransport } from \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js\";"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "import {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "CallToolRequestSchema,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "ListResourcesRequestSchema,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "ListToolsRequestSchema,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "ReadResourceRequestSchema"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "} from \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/types.js\";"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "import pg from \"pg\";"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const { Pool } = pg;"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "// Initialize db pool using environment configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const pool = new Pool({"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "ssl: { rejectUnauthorized: true }"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "});"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const server = new Server("
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "name: \"secure-postgres-mcp\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "version: \"1.0.0\""
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "},"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "capabilities: {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "resources: {},"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "tools: {}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": ");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "// Register resource discovery"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "server.setRequestHandler(ListResourcesRequestSchema, async () => {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "return {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "resources: ["
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "uri: \"database://schema/customer_summary\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "name: \"Customer Summary Table Structure\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "mimeType: \"text/plain\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "description: \"Exposes available columns and data types in public.customers table\""
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "};"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "});"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "// Read table metadata"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "server.setRequestHandler(ReadResourceRequestSchema, async (request) => {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "if (request.params.uri === \"database://schema/customer_summary\") {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const result = await pool.query("
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "`SELECT column_name, data_type"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "FROM information_schema.columns"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "WHERE table_name = 'customers' AND table_schema = 'public';`"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": ");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const schemaText = result.rows"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": ".map(row => `${row.column_name}: ${row.data_type}`)"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": ".join(\"\\n\");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "return {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "contents: ["
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "uri: request.params.uri,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "mimeType: \"text/plain\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "text: `Table Schema [customers]:\\n${schemaText}`"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "};"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "throw new Error(\"Unknown resource URI\");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "});"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "// Expose query tool"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "server.setRequestHandler(ListToolsRequestSchema, async () => {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "return {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "tools: ["
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "name: \"get_customer_orders\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "description: \"Retrieves orders for a customer ID. Exposes only safe order metadata.\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "inputSchema: {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "type: \"object\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "properties: {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "customerId: {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "type: \"integer\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "description: \"Numeric database ID of the target customer\""
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "},"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "limit: {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "type: \"integer\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "description: \"Max rows to return (Limit 50)\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "default: 10"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "},"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "required: [\"customerId\"]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "};"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "});"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "// Execute parameterized query"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "server.setRequestHandler(CallToolRequestSchema, async (request) => {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "if (request.params.name === \"get_customer_orders\") {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const customerId = request.params.arguments?.customerId;"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const limit = Math.min(Number(request.params.arguments?.limit || 10), 50);"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "try {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const query = `"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "SELECT order_id, order_date, total_amount, status"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "FROM orders"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "WHERE customer_id = $1"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "ORDER BY order_date DESC"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "LIMIT $2;"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "`;"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const result = await pool.query(query, [customerId, limit]);"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "return {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "content: ["
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "type: \"text\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "text: JSON.stringify(result.rows, null, 2)"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "};"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "} catch (dbError) {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "console.error(\"Database query failed:\", dbError);"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "return {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "isError: true,"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "content: ["
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "{"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "type: \"text\","
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "text: \"Error executing query safely: Database operation failed.\""
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "};"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "throw new Error(\"Tool not found\");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "});"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "async function main() {"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "const transport = new StdioServerTransport();"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "await server.connect(transport);"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "console.error(\"Secure PostgreSQL MCP Server initialized\");"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "}"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "main().catch(console.error);"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "```"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "## Check Your Understanding"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 1: Which implementation pattern best mitigates the risk of SQL injection inside an MCP server that executes queries on behalf of an agent?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A. Using regex to block string keywords like 'DROP' or 'DELETE'."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "B. Encrypting database traffic using TLS 1.3."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "C. Utilizing database user accounts that have read-only permissions."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "D. Enforcing strict parameterized queries (prepared statements) for all inputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Answer Feedback: D is correct. Parameterized queries/prepared statements separate SQL command logic from user-provided data inputs, rendering SQL injection payloads inert. While C is a vital practice, it limits the blast radius but doesn't prevent injection."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 2: What is the main utility of exposing table schemas dynamically as read-only MCP resources?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A. It allows the model to gain an accurate structural understanding of available columns and data types without executing raw queries."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "B. It increases database write throughput significantly."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "C. It bypasses database authentication routines."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "D. It compile-checks SQL code before compilation."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Answer Feedback: A is correct. By providing table structures as resources (e.g. database://schema/table), the model can learn what columns exist, ensuring it generates valid tool invocation parameters."
    }
  ]
}